# Phase 4 — Analytics, Security Hardening, Full Test Coverage, Polish & Documentation

Final phase of the Udemy Course Finder. Upgrade the analytics page with interactive time-series charts, harden the security posture (rate limiting refinements, token blacklisting via Redis, CORS review, structured logging), achieve comprehensive test coverage across all three services (backend, frontend, scraper), and produce final documentation.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Analytics Time-Series Charts**: The ARU (Section 4.9) specifies *"courses added over time, per-source yield"*. I will add a **Recharts**-based time-series line chart to the Analytics page showing courses added per day (last 30 days) and a stacked area chart of per-provider yield over time. This requires a new backend endpoint `GET /analytics/time-series` that aggregates `courses.createdAt` by day. **Please confirm this scope and the 30-day default window.**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Redis Token Blacklisting**: The current `logout()` is a no-op (line 59 of [auth.service.ts](file:///home/akai/Desktop/Udemy%20Course%20Finder/backend/src/auth/auth.service.ts) says *"Full token blacklisting will use Redis in Phase 4"*). I will implement a Redis-backed blacklist so that on logout, the JWT's `jti` is stored in Redis with a TTL matching the token's remaining lifetime. The `JwtAuthGuard` will check this blacklist on every request. **Please confirm this approach.**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Rate Limiting Tiers**: Currently the `ThrottlerModule` is configured globally with a single rule (`100 req / 60s`). The ARU (Section 14) specifies *"rate limiting applied to auth endpoints"* specifically. I will add a stricter rate limit on auth endpoints (`5 req / 60s` for `/auth/login`) via a `@Throttle()` decorator override, while keeping the global limit for all other routes. **Please confirm these thresholds.**

> [!WARNING]
> **Test Scope**: There are currently **zero backend unit tests** (`src/**/*.spec.ts` — none exist) and the scraper has 2 test files covering pipeline stages and URL parsing. Phase 4 will add unit tests for all backend services, repositories, controllers, DTOs, and guards. E2E tests will cover full API flows (login → CRUD → logout). Frontend tests are excluded from this phase since no testing framework (Jest/Vitest) is configured in the frontend `package.json`. **Please confirm if frontend tests should be included (this would require additional setup).**

> [!WARNING]
> **Structured Logging**: The backend currently uses NestJS's built-in `Logger` across all services. I will add `nestjs-pino` (Pino-based structured JSON logging) so logs are machine-parseable when running in Docker, with human-readable pretty-print in development. This changes log output format. **Please confirm this addition.**

