## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q1 — Analytics Date Range**: Should the time-series analytics support configurable date ranges (7d / 14d / 30d / 90d / All time) via a dropdown, or is a fixed 30-day window sufficient for Phase 4?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q2 — Password Change Endpoint**: The Phase 3 Settings page mentions a password change form, but no `PATCH /auth/password` endpoint exists on the backend. Should Phase 4 add this endpoint (hashed password update with current-password verification), or was it deferred intentionally?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q3 — Redis Cache Layer**: The ARU (Section 7) specifies *"Redis caches expensive/frequent reads (dashboard stats, search results) with sensible TTLs, invalidated on new scrape ingestion."* Currently, Redis is only used for BullMQ. Should Phase 4 add Redis caching for `GET /courses/stats`, `GET /analytics/overview`, and `GET /courses/search` results, or defer to a future optimization pass?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q4 — History Clear Endpoint**: The Phase 3 History page has a "Clear History" button, but there's no `DELETE /history` endpoint on the backend. Should Phase 4 add `DELETE /history` (clear all history for the authenticated user)?

